cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS

The paper deals with the problem of achieving the capacity of the AWGN broadcast channel using coded modulation, which is a topic in information theory and communication engineering. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the design of multilevel codes and bit-interleaved construction, which are techniques used in digital signal processing and coding theory, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Signal Processing) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper presents simulation results, which involve the implementation and evaluation of algorithms, making cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a possible sub-category.
